ce:section.ce:para:
To further investigate the effects of the purification process on R-CDs, their fluorescence emission, absorption spectra, and optical bandgap were analyzed. A comparative analysis of R-CDs before (polymer filtration only) and after additional purification by dialysis (polymer filtration followed by dialysis – MW8000-14000) revealed minor variations. Under excitation at a wavelength of 670 nm, two prominent emission peaks were observed at 682.6 nm (I1
                        ) and 722.8 nm (I2
                        ) before dialysis (Fig. S2(a)), and at 674.2 nm (I1D
                        ) and 722.8 nm (I2D
                        ) after dialysis (Fig. S2(d)). Notably, only the I1
                         peak exhibited a slight blue shift of 0.02 eV following dialysis, suggesting a reduction in particle size, while the I2
                         peak remained unchanged, indicating that the surface state characteristics were largely unaffected. This interpretation is further supported by a 0.02 eV increase in the optical bandgap, from 1.81 eV before dialysis to 1.83 eV after dialysis (Fig. S1(f)), which is consistent with the quantum confinement effect.
